humiliate /hjuːˈmɪlɪˌeɪt/

(humiliating,humiliated,humiliates) 

1. V-T To humiliate someone means to say or do something which makes them feel ashamed or stupid. 使蒙羞 

例： She had been beaten and humiliated by her husband. 她曾被丈夫殴打和羞辱。 

2. humiliated ADJ 感到丢脸的 

例： I have never felt so humiliated in my life. 我一生中从未感到这么丢脸过。

